# Harness Operational Rules & Agent Guidelines

You are operating inside a repository managed by the **Harness** framework. All tasks, specs, stories, and execution traces must follow the structured Harness workflow.

---

## 🔄 1. The Harness Development Loop
Every task or feature request must strictly follow these sequential phases:

1.  **Feature Intake**: Classify risk level (`tiny`, `normal`, `high-risk`) via `harness-cli intake`.
2.  **Product Contract (PRD)**: Elicit requirements and write a PRD to `docs/product/`.
3.  **Story Decomposition**: Slice the feature into granular stories and register them via `harness-cli story add`.
4.  **Implementation**: Write clean, modular code following architectural boundary rules (`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`).
5.  **Quality Proof (Tests)**: Write unit/integration/E2E tests and register pass flags via `harness-cli story update`.
6.  **Verification**: Execute `harness-cli story verify <id>` or `verify-all` to run verification commands automatically.
7.  **Execution Trace**: Log the session trace to the database via `harness-cli trace`.

---

## 👥 2. Specialized Agent Personas
Before starting a sub-task, read and adopt the respective instructions under `.agents/personas/`:
- **Product Manager**: [pm.md](file:///.agents/personas/pm.md) (Intake & Stories)
- **Business Analyst**: [ba.md](file:///.agents/personas/ba.md) (Functional Specs & Acceptance Criteria)
- **Frontend Engineer**: [fe.md](file:///.agents/personas/fe.md) (Interactive & Responsive UI)
- **Backend Engineer**: [be.md](file:///.agents/personas/be.md) (API, DB Migrations, Security)
- **QA Engineer**: [qa.md](file:///.agents/personas/qa.md) (Test Suites & Verification proofs)

---

## 🛠️ 3. Quick CLI Command Reference
Use the local `harness-cli` binary at `scripts/bin/harness-cli`:

| Action | Command |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Intake Classification** | `./scripts/bin/harness-cli intake --type "<type>" --summary "<text>" --lane <tiny\|normal\|high-risk>` |
| **Add Story** | `./scripts/bin/harness-cli story add --id <id> --title "<title>" --lane <lane>` |
| **Update Story Proof** | `./scripts/bin/harness-cli story update --id <id> --status implemented --evidence "<msg>" --unit 1 --integration 1` |
| **Verify Single Story** | `./scripts/bin/harness-cli story verify <id>` |
| **Verify All Stories** | `./scripts/bin/harness-cli story verify-all` |
| **Log Agent Trace** | `./scripts/bin/harness-cli trace --summary "<text>" --story <id> --agent <name> --outcome completed` |
| **Check Test Matrix** | `./scripts/bin/harness-cli query matrix` |
| **Check Stats** | `./scripts/bin/harness-cli query stats` |

---

## 🎨 4. Design & Aesthetic Rules (For Frontend Tasks)
If implementing frontend features, you must follow these styling rules:
- **Rich Aesthetics**: Utilizesleek dark modes, modern typography (Google Fonts like Outfit, Inter), glassmorphism, and smooth gradients.
- **Micro-animations**: Add transitions (`transition: all 0.3s ease`) on hovers, focuses, and active states.
- **Responsiveness**: Implement mobile-first layouts using CSS Flexbox and CSS Grid.
- **No default colors**: Avoid standard primary colors; use curated, harmonious color palettes (HSL).
